This paper deals with understanding user behavior on social media, which falls under the category of social media analysis. The use of computational mechanics and echo state networks for modeling user behavior suggests a focus on machine learning and data analysis, which falls under the categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and data structures and algorithms (cs.SD). The paper also discusses the challenges faced in applying predictive models to dynamic social data, which suggests a focus on social computing (cs.SOC) and cybernetics (cs.CY). Finally, the use of Twitter data suggests a focus on social media analysis (cs.SI).
